manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Dual Band Wi-Fi RE500X offers fast speed dual band Wi-Fi, delivering combined speeds of up to 1.5 Gbps. It ensures sufficient bandwidth for gaming online and HD streaming.¹ 4 high-performance amplifiers, we got you covered Enjoy 4K streaming in whatever room you’re in thanks to RE500X’s 4 high-performance amplifiers. RE500X sends out strong signals to those hard-to-cover areas.

More efficient data with OFDMA Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiple Access helps integrate the data of different end devices for higher efficiency.² Strong, Targeted WiFi with Beamforming Find the direction of your phone or laptop and accelerate your signal strength.

DIY WiFi Every home is different. That’s why our AX range extender provides you with a flexible array of options to custom create your own high-speed WiFi. Adjustable WiFi Coverage Keep your internet focused on a single room or blanket an entire floor with WiFi by picking between 3 strength levels on the Tether app.

Built-In Access Point Mode RE500X is more than just a wireless range extender. Simply plug an Ethernet cable into its port to easily turn that wired connection into a high-speed dual-band wireless signal. A Better WiFi Experience with OneMesh OneMesh uses your compatible router and range extender to form a mesh WiFi network. It allows you to roam freely without connecting to a new network or dropping your connection and only requires one name and password to connect.

Find the Right Spot for the Best Connection Stop guessing where you should put your range extender. The intelligent signal indicator will help you find the optimal location for the best WiFi signal. Easy setup with Tether app Setup is fast and easy with the Tether app. Download the app to your Android or iOS mobile device and it will guide you through setup and configuration with clear direction and simple visuals.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So easy to install...and it works fantastic
reviews.reviewText: I have tried numerous wifi "extenders" over the past 5 years or so, and none of them worked in contrast to the product claims by the manufacturer. I recently upgraded my router to a TP-Link AX21 (AX1800) wifi 6 model. I get great coverage inside my home, but venture outside onto my terrace and its signal could not produce a reliable connection. I was contemplating scrapping the router and going with a mesh router with satellites. But I just bought the router, was happy with it overall and I paid $100 USD for it. Then I began my search anew for an extender that would work with my router. Then I found this little baby for $70 on Amazon. I decided to give it a try, especially given Amazon's liberal return policies. I received the unit quickly and decided to pair it to my TP-Link router via the WPS mode. I plugged it in near my router. Step 1: press the WPS button on the router. Step 2: within 2 minutes, hold the WPS button on the extender for 2 seconds. Step 3: wait up to 2 minutes for pairing to be complete. Well, it worked flawlessly. I moved the extender to an AC outlet next to the door leading outside. I now got full wifi signal outside in either 2.4GHz or 5GHz. Also note, 5 GHz is great unless it is restricted by walls. So in the past, any signal I did receive outside had to be 2.4GHz. Now I can use either, and the connection strength on my iPhone 12 mini is great outside the house. Pages load instantly. YouTube videos stream flawlessly with no stuttering or lost connection. I could't be happier.Please note that the AX 21 TP-Link router has a design feature they call One Mesh. This extender also supports One Mesh. So unlike the extenders I have tried in the past, this extender maintains the same router channel name and SSID. So roaming is a seamless experience. I advise anyone looking for a good extender to consider this unit. But research is needed to make sure this extender is compatible with your router. I bought this extender because it specifically states it is One Mesh, and even bears the moniker "AX1800", undoubtedly with reference to my TP-Link AX1800 (AX21). Always choose an extender that allows for maintaining the same router channel name AND SSID. Other routers also have a feature to mesh with their extenders, so start your search there. Hope this helps!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Long Reboot Time, But Otherwise a Good Purchase
reviews.reviewText: NOTE: The RE600X extender has a very long reboot time, at least as compared to the old TP-Link RE220 extender it replaces. About 4 minutes. I initially thought the unit was defective because the power LED would flash forever, but it's just a long reboot time span with this unit.Upgraded our home WiFi from the old workhorse combo of a TP-Link Archer C7 (v5) router and TP-Link RE220 range extender (OneMesh system enabled), to a WiFi 6 setup with a TP-Link AX1800 (Archer AX21) router and TPLink RE600X range extender both purchased via The TP-Link Store here on Amazon.So far, very satisfied. The router was easy to setup. The range extender setup was also easy and uses the same layout as the RE220 it replaced so it was a familiar setup. To test the RE600X I checked WiFi connection speed on my Samasung Galaxy Note 20 5G (a WiFi 6 device) while about 7 feet (2.1 meters) from the extender. 1.1 Gbps !! Impressive, but that's also pretty close proximity. House is 1800 sq ft single level and the router is in bedroom at one corner of house and the extender in kitchen at the opposite end, so they are about the diagonal breadth of the house apart. Coverage is excellent. I would have to run a LAN cable to living room to locate the router more centrally (which admittedly, is ideal) but as it is, the opposite ends of house arrangement the router and extender are set in covers the premises with enough throughput such that we're getting about 185 Mbps on internet speed tests if a device is midway in between the router and extender, that's with 400Mbps broadband service. WiFi in general just tends to murder your subscribed Mbps speed rate you're buying from your ISP the farther you get from the router, at least on this middle tier class of home router. The extender is intentionally on kitchen exterior wall that faces swimming pool area outside. The old RE220 was getting signal to the pool area but about 50% strength. Haven't gone out there yet to test if the RE600X extender is exceeding that, but confident it probably is since it solidly beats the old RE220's performance inside the house.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy set up
reviews.reviewText: Easy set up just download the app. Get an Ethernet cable makes your speed way faster. Connection is always good. My router is getting 600mps and in the room where I have the extender I’m getting about 450-500mps. My ping is at 10-15 and no lagging for gaming. Downloading games is fast too. Like I said Ethernet cable probably cat6-8. But overall I recommend this product if you’re having wifi trouble in the house.

We have an extremely poor WiFi signal that doesn’t reach downstairs at all. We placed the Wifi extension downstairs and our Firestick now works easily. We can watch our Dodgers games and the Tony Award.Tenemos una señal WiFi extremadamente pobre que no llega a la planta baja en absoluto. Pusimos la extensión Wifi abajo y nuestro Firestick ahora funciona fácilmente. Podemos ver nuestros partidos de los Dodgers y el Premio Tony.

reviews.reviewTitle: Facil de instalar y tener un extensor de red rapidamente. Baja estabilidad de red y baja velocidad
reviews.reviewText: Es un equipo que compre para sustituir a otro modelo de TP link el RE650. Este equipo tiene la opcion de onemesh, que te permite unificar tu red con diversos extensores y que tus equipos se conecten al mas potente para ellos.Es muy facil instalarlo, en cuestion de 10 minutos ya esta listo y funcionando.Desgraciadamente el onemesh no funciona tan bien y los equipos se conectan indiscriminadamente a cualquiera de los extensores y al router principal. Con esto a veces la conexion se realiza al extensor mas lejano, bajando el rendimiento.Ademas de lo anterior, la potencia de estos equipos es mas baja que el RE650, estando pegado a ellos, no logran sobrepasar 200Mbps de conexion, cuando el RE650 alcanza los 500Mbps en mismas condiciones.Si la veloidad de tu red de internet es menor a 200Mbps, tal vez te funcione sin mermas en velocidad, pero si es superior a eso, jamas lo alcanzaras con este equipo.Ademas es mas caro que el RE650.

reviews.reviewTitle: Funktioniert vermutlich aber nicht bei mir.
reviews.reviewText: Habe eine Fritzbox 7490, die Installation war recht einfach, der TP-Link WiFi 6 Extender harmonierte aber nicht wirklich mit meiner FritzBox. Die erhöhte Reichweite, na ja sagen wir mal unwesentlich. Vergleichbar mit einem WiFi 6 Repeater von AVM, aber es kam nach einigen Tagen immer häufiger zu WLAN Aussetzern. Also Repeater und Extender neu installiert, keine Besserung. Habe dann einen AVM WiFi 6 Repeater installiert, alles läuft gut. Ich denke der TP-Link WiFi 6 Extender ist grundsätzlich ein guter Extender, aber nicht in meiner WLAN-Umgebung. Gerät zurückgesendet.
Lo recomiendo ampliamente por la facilidad de instalar. He comprado otros cuyas instrucciones de instalar son malas y difíciles
Cumple con lo que dice, mejora la conexión en diferentes puntos de la casa
